structure.unit: DIVISION OF INSURANCE AND INSURANCE GENERALLY (Superseded)

law.history: Repealed 1950 Ky. Acts ch. 21, sec. 2. -- Repealed and reenacted 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 106, sec. 13, effective June 17, 1948. -- Created 1946 Ky. Acts ch. 100, sec. 10(a), (b) and (c), effective October 1, 1947.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Rules and plans for recording and reporting of loss and expense experience; interchange of rating plan data; consultation with other states.
